b:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Who Should Choose Which?"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"The ideal user for each platform differs considerably. JetBrains AI is best suited for JetBrains IDE users, Java/Kotlin developers, making it a strong choice if you fall into any of these categories. Sourcegraph Cody, meanwhile, shines for large codebases, teams needing codebase wide context, which means it may be the better pick if your needs align with those use cases.\n\nFounded in 2023, JetBrains AI describes itself as \"AI assistant built into JetBrains IDEs.\" Sourcegraph Cody, established in 2023, positions itself as \"AI that understands your entire codebase.\" Both platforms have been in the market for a similar duration, giving each ample time to refine their offerings and build a loyal user base."}]]}]
c:["$","div",null,{"className":"verdict-box","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Our Verdict"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"After analyzing all the data, **Sourcegraph Cody** comes out slightly ahead in this comparison, thanks to higher user ratings (8.0 vs 7.0), more competitive pricing, availability of a free plan. However, this does not mean JetBrains AI is a poor choice — far from it. JetBrains AI excels in its own right, particularly for JetBrains IDE users and Java/Kotlin developers.\n\nOur recommendation: if you value deep codebase understanding, go with Sourcegraph Cody. If deep jetbrains ide integration matters more to you, JetBrains AI is the way to go. Either way, both are solid platforms that have earned their place in the market."}]]}]
